Key Match Events: Steve Mounie scored for Benin in the 50th minute.
Junior Olaitan scored a penalty for Benin in the 62nd minute.
Al Badri scored a penalty for Libya in the 9th minute.
Shafshuf, Mukhtar Al Shremi, Al Badri, Abo Shaalah, and Arteeba received yellow cards for Libya.
Pre-Game Insights: Benin and Libya return to action in Group D of the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers.
This will be the first meeting between the two nations since November 2018.
Benin were outclassed by Nigeria in their Group D opener, losing 3-0.
Libya were held to a 1-1 draw by Rwanda in their AFCON qualifying campaign opener.
